		(property "SolderSlack Pin Current Facts" "{\"version\":1,\"source\":\"solderslack.datasheet\",\"productCode\":\"C83846\",\"productModel\":\"SMBJ36CA\",\"pins\":{\"1\":{\"pinFunction\":\"1\",\"facts\":[{\"kind\":\"typical_current_a\",\"currentA\":0.001,\"direction\":\"bidirectional\",\"scope\":\"load_path\",\"basis\":\"datasheet\",\"confidence\":\"high\",\"evidence\":\"Test Current (IT): current used to measure the breakdown voltage (VBR).\",\"conditions\":\"Breakdown voltage measurement test current.\"},{\"kind\":\"max_operating_current_a\",\"currentA\":0.000001,\"direction\":\"bidirectional\",\"scope\":\"load_path\",\"basis\":\"datasheet\",\"confidence\":\"high\",\"evidence\":\"Maximum Reverse Leakage (IR): maximum current leakage when the device is at the stand-off voltage.\",\"conditions\":\"VR = 36 V.\"},{\"kind\":\"absolute_max_current_a\",\"currentA\":10.4,\"direction\":\"bidirectional\",\"scope\":\"load_path\",\"basis\":\"datasheet\",\"confidence\":\"high\",\"evidence\":\"Maximum Peak Pulse Current (IPP): maximum allowable transient current for a 10/1000 µs waveform.\",\"conditions\":\"10/1000 µs pulse waveform.\"}]},\"2\":{\"pinFunction\":\"2\",\"facts\":[{\"kind\":\"typical_current_a\",\"currentA\":0.001,\"direction\":\"bidirectional\",\"scope\":\"load_path\",\"basis\":\"datasheet\",\"confidence\":\"high\",\"evidence\":\"Test Current (IT): current used to measure the breakdown voltage (VBR).\",\"conditions\":\"Breakdown voltage measurement test current.\"},{\"kind\":\"max_operating_current_a\",\"currentA\":0.000001,\"direction\":\"bidirectional\",\"scope\":\"load_path\",\"basis\":\"datasheet\",\"confidence\":\"high\",\"evidence\":\"Maximum Reverse Leakage (IR): maximum current leakage when the device is at the stand-off voltage.\",\"conditions\":\"VR = 36 V.\"},{\"kind\":\"absolute_max_current_a\",\"currentA\":10.4,\"direction\":\"bidirectional\",\"scope\":\"load_path\",\"basis\":\"datasheet\",\"confidence\":\"high\",\"evidence\":\"Maximum Peak Pulse Current (IPP): maximum allowable transient current for a 10/1000 µs waveform.\",\"conditions\":\"10/1000 µs pulse waveform.\"}]}},\"notes\":[\"Peak Forward Surge Current (IFSM) of 100 A is omitted because the datasheet note says it applies to unidirectional devices only, while SMBJ36CA is bi-directional.\",\"No continuous normal operating current rating is provided for this protection device.\"]}"
			(at 0 0 180)
